<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFFAFFD1FF6BFA88FDC8F995" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFFAFFD1FF6BFA88FDC8F995" blockId="32.[151,1127,1390,1605]" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFAFFD1FF6BFA88FEBBFA35" bold="true" box="[151,261,1390,1413]" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFAFFD1FEF5FA88FE09FA35" author="BOHEMAN" box="[265,439,1390,1413]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" refId="ref48022" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1862: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Quartus. (Supplementum). Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, vi + 504 pp." type="book" year="1862">BOHEMAN (1862)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFAFFD1FDD9FA88FD47FA35" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[549,761,1390,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Porphyraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picina">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFAFFD1FDD9FA88FD47FA35" box="[549,761,1390,1413]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">Porphyraspis picina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and differentiated it from 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFAFFD1FBF9FA88FBD8FA35" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1850" box="[1029,1126,1390,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Porphyraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFAFFD1FBF9FA88FBD8FA35" box="[1029,1126,1390,1413]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">P. rugosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the darker colour of elytra. I have compared 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFFAFFD1FD5CFA68FD66FA15" box="[672,728,1422,1445]" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">types</typeStatus>
of both taxa and in my opinion they are conspecific as they have identical formation of elytral costae, punctation, and shape of pronotum. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFAFFD1FEF2FA28FE4EFA55" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1850" box="[270,496,1486,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Porphyraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFAFFD1FEF2FA28FE4EFA55" box="[270,496,1486,1509]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">Porphyraspis rugosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on a teneral, partially sclerotized and coloured specimen, resulting in a paler colouration than fully sclerotized 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFAFFD1FCBEFA08FC21F9B5" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[834,927,1518,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Porphyraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picina">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFAFFD1FCBEFA08FC21F9B5" box="[834,927,1518,1541]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">P. picina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For these reasons I synonymize the latter taxon with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFAFFD1FDF7F9E8FDD1F995" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1850" box="[523,623,1550,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Porphyraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFAFFD1FDF7F9E8FDD1F995" box="[523,623,1550,1573]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">P. rugosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
